What the heck is going on here?

34
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:03,880
[Episode 3]

35
00:02:04,940 --> 00:02:08,490
[1 Week Ago]

36
00:02:08,490 --> 00:02:10,940
Say, Sosuke...

37
00:02:10,940 --> 00:02:14,990
Do you want to get back together with your ex?

38
00:02:14,990 --> 00:02:17,470
Huh? What are you talking about?

39
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:23,150
The woman in that photo is currently my first love's girlfriend.

40
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:24,890
Come again?

41
00:02:24,890 --> 00:02:27,000
Hang on a sec.

42
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:33,210
Your ex is my ex's current boyfriend?

43
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:37,870
That's right. What a small world indeed.

44
00:02:37,870 --> 00:02:41,420
I'll do you a favor and hook you up with Hoshi.

45
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:43,860
So help me in return.

46
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:46,660
It's your fault we broke up in the first place.

47
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:48,500
You lied to me about being pregnant.

48
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:51,420
Right back at you. You were two-timing me.

49
00:02:51,420 --> 00:02:55,730
- That's because...
- You thought you could start things over with Hoshi.

50
00:02:55,730 --> 00:03:00,990
But she latched onto another guy quickly, and that annoys you.

51
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:02,650
Am I wrong?

52
00:03:02,650 --> 00:03:05,300
You wanted my help. What do I have to do?

53
00:03:10,130 --> 00:03:13,020
First off, invite her to dinner.

54
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:15,950
Even if I do, Koyori won't agree.

55
00:03:15,950 --> 00:03:19,880
If it's for work, she can't exactly turn you down, no?

56
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:25,170
Just say you both need to attend dinner with a client.

57
00:03:25,170 --> 00:03:30,160
Then I'll get my colleague to set up a meeting with Hijiri,

58
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:33,360
and go meet him on their behalf that day.

59
00:03:35,210 --> 00:03:39,320
I'm once again reminded of what a terrifying woman you are.

60
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:43,020
What? That's mean.

61
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:48,220
Do you really like this Hijiri guy that much?

62
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:52,550
Yup.

63
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:59,370
Could this really be such a coincidence?

64
00:03:59,370 --> 00:04:02,040
There's something fishy about this.

65
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:08,020
But Yoshida and Saito most likely haven't met before.

66
00:04:08,020 --> 00:04:10,550
I shouldn't be suspicious them.

67
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:13,350
Koyori, stop.

68
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:17,230
Do you plan to finish the entire bottle all on your own?

69
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:20,930
You know you get carried away when you're deep in thought.

70
00:04:20,930 --> 00:04:23,870
- Stick to drinking water.
- Fine.

71
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:29,170
Mr. Yoshida, I'm surprised you call Hoshi by her first name.

72
00:04:29,170 --> 00:04:32,510
Yes, but she gets mad at me when I do that.

73
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:34,740
It's an old habit I can't shake off.

74
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:38,100
- Mr. Yoshidaãƒ¼
- Wait, could it be that you two...

75
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:41,060
Yes. We were dating until recently.

76
00:04:41,060 --> 00:04:44,270
- Did you have to mention that?
- There's no use hiding it.

77
00:04:44,270 --> 00:04:50,160
Which means we're currently sitting with your ex and current boyfriend?

78
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:54,030
This is Harukaze carpaccio in two-color style.

79
00:04:54,670 --> 00:04:59,860
I'm so sorry, Hoshi. I shouldn't have asked to join you two.

80
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:02,660
This must be awkward for you.

81
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:07,980
It's fine. Thanks to you, we didn't have to cancel this reservation.

82
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:14,040
By the way, were the three of you close in junior high?

83
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:18,390
- Kind of.
- In fact, the two of us also dated back then.

84
00:05:18,390 --> 00:05:22,870
- Right?
- What? Really?

85
00:05:22,870 --> 00:05:25,080
This brings back memories.

86
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:30,100
Hijiri, you waited for me at the shoe shelves to confess. Right?

87
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:34,320
Hijiri was the one who took the initiative? I didn't know that.

88
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:37,800
I was dumped a few months later, though. We had exams to focus on.

89
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,230
Right, I did.

90
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:44,150
- But I still regret it.
- Huh?

91
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:46,700
Sometimes I wonder if we hadn't broken up back then,

92
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:51,990
maybe we would still be together now.

93
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,410
It's pointless to think of the "what ifs".

94
00:05:58,410 --> 00:06:00,220
True, but...

95
00:06:00,220 --> 00:06:03,590
The one I'm dating now... is Koyori.

96
00:06:04,730 --> 00:06:08,120
Jeez, of course I know that.

97
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:13,850
There are many things I regret about the past.

98
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:19,050
So now, I want to cherish the present. To live without regrets.

99
00:06:22,170 --> 00:06:24,130
I feel like crying.

100
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:28,920
Excuse me. I need to go to the washroom.

101
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:32,400
Hey, are you okay?

102
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,090
I'll go and check on her.

103
00:06:44,450 --> 00:06:48,850
I thought I knew everything about Hijiri, but I didn't.

104
00:06:48,850 --> 00:06:51,150
I want to cherish the present.

105
00:06:51,150 --> 00:06:55,060
That's why those words moved me.

106
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,560
Hoshi?

107
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,910
Are you all right?

108
00:06:59,910 --> 00:07:02,280
If you don't mind, use this.

109
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:05,020
Thanks.

110
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:10,180
That day was when we first met each other. Right?

111
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:13,280
I hope we can start over.

112
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,820
Request denied.

113
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:22,410
I didn't expect you to reject me on her behalf.

114
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:26,690
That's because Koyori seemed to be at a loss for words.

115
00:07:29,940 --> 00:07:34,310
She started going out with you after that, right?

116
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:36,200
That's right.

117
00:07:39,810 --> 00:07:42,060
Damn...

118
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:43,810
What is it?

119
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:47,200
I'm shocked.

120
00:07:48,340 --> 00:07:52,330
Koyori told me she didn't want a breakup.

121
00:07:52,330 --> 00:07:57,190
Yet she started dating you right after.

122
00:07:57,190 --> 00:08:01,000
Was she lying to me or what?

123
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:09,040
I don't really understand.

124
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:13,570
You love Koyori, don't you?

125
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,290
Yeah, so?

126
00:08:16,290 --> 00:08:19,410
Then don't speak ill of the woman you love.

127
00:08:25,910 --> 00:08:27,460
I'll take my leave first.

128
00:08:30,530 --> 00:08:35,240
Here is my share of the cost.

129
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:43,620
- Koyori, let's go home.
- You sure?

130
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:46,090
It's fine. This isn't work-related anyways.

131
00:08:46,090 --> 00:08:47,750
Thanks.

132
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:49,630
- Sorry about that.
- I'm terribly sorry.

133
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:04,990
Hijiri, what's wrong?

134
00:09:06,210 --> 00:09:08,240
Nothing in particular.

135
00:09:09,470 --> 00:09:11,100
But...

136
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,550
Did he say something mean to you?

137
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:30,080
It's my mom.

138
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:34,000
She and Dad are down with the flu, and they want me home.

139
00:09:34,730 --> 00:09:38,630
I'll be fine on my own, so go check on them.

140
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:39,830
Thanks for understanding.

141
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:41,460
- Sorry about that.
- It's okay.

142
00:09:41,460 --> 00:09:43,990
See you.

143
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,180
[Magnifique game]

144
00:10:01,180 --> 00:10:04,200
That woman is clearly targeting your boyfriend.

145
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,280
I know, right?

146
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:10,080
But since she knows we're together, why go through all that trouble?

147
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:13,840
Some people want something because it belongs to someone else.

148
00:10:14,770 --> 00:10:17,960
I see...

149
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:22,650
That's why you should be firm and stay away from her.

150
00:10:22,650 --> 00:10:24,540
They said mackerel or bonito would do.

151
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:28,260
Mackerel? No, dried sardines are definitely the correct choice.

152
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:30,060
I'll pass on your enthusiasm.

153
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:33,110
Please do.

154
00:10:40,850 --> 00:10:45,660
- Koyoriãƒ¼
- I won't go to such dinners anymore. So stop it.

155
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:57,800
If you do anything to hurt the person I love, I won't forgive you.

156
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:03,990
The person you love, huh?

157
00:11:03,990 --> 00:11:06,960
Then don't speak ill of the woman you love.

158
00:11:11,990 --> 00:11:14,840
- I'm done.
- What?

159
00:11:16,060 --> 00:11:23,250
People my age hardly say stuff like "the person I love".

160
00:11:26,070 --> 00:11:29,600
I'm sorry, Hoshi.

161
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,010
Huh?

162
00:11:43,190 --> 00:11:44,760
Thanks for the other day.

163
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:48,960
It's a pity I didn't get to chat more with you after that.

164
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:53,110
If you're free tonight, want to catch up over dinner?

165
00:11:57,730 --> 00:12:01,130
The one I'm dating now is Koyori.

166
00:12:13,330 --> 00:12:15,500
Hoshi, over here.

167
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,610
Hey, there.

168
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:20,220
I went ahead and ordered a drink. The food here is good.

169
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:22,330
You must be hungry.

170
00:12:23,430 --> 00:12:25,070
I'll just have a drink.

171
00:12:25,070 --> 00:12:28,110
- One coffee, please.
- Of course.

172
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:33,450
I came only because I have something to tell you.

173
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:37,040
Is that so?

174
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:44,340
I figured it would be easier to talk about more... touchy topics over food, though.

175
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:46,620
Touchy topics?

176
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:53,150
Hijiri had approached me during our reunion the other day.

177
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:59,320
I was getting a little tipsy and left for some fresh air when Hijiri came after me.

178
00:12:59,970 --> 00:13:07,350
He said, "Let's do what we couldn't do in junior high," and tried to kiss me.

179
00:13:07,350 --> 00:13:10,440
He did that even though he already had you.

180
00:13:11,260 --> 00:13:13,570
Though I say we broke up because of "exams,"

181
00:13:13,570 --> 00:13:18,910
the real reason was because I saw him eyeing other girls.

182
00:13:18,910 --> 00:13:21,320
Thank you for waiting. Here is your coffee.

183
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:30,750
You two bought these as a pair, didn't you?

184
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:39,140
Hijiri was laughing, you know? He called you childish for being happy with a keychain.

185
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:41,830
How did that end up with you?

186
00:13:41,830 --> 00:13:46,210
Hijiri said he didn't need it anymore, so he gave it to me.

187
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,590
Hoshi,

188
00:13:59,590 --> 00:14:01,490
I'm saying this for your own good.

189
00:14:01,490 --> 00:14:03,910
You should break up with Hijiãƒ¼

190
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:06,900
Hijiri wouldn't do such a thing.

191
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:10,190
So are you saying I'm lying?

192
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:13,420
Yes, I am. Sorry.

193
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:15,580
How can you be so sure?

194
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:17,860
Did Hijiri saying something about me to you?

195
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:23,140
No, he didn't. I just trust Hijiri. That's all.

196
00:14:23,140 --> 00:14:25,370
Then how do you explain this?

197
00:14:27,110 --> 00:14:32,960
He probably dropped it and you picked it up.

198
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:38,230
- Hey, are you okay?
- I'll go check on her.

199
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:43,410
Thanks.

200
00:14:44,060 --> 00:14:46,180
- Sorry about that.
- I'm terribly sorry.

201
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:03,770
How can you trust him without testing his love for you?

202
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:07,390
- I bet you don't love Hijiri after all, do you?
- Pardon?

203
00:15:07,390 --> 00:15:12,130
From the way you behave around Hijiri, you don't look like you love him.

204
00:15:12,130 --> 00:15:13,970
I do love him.

205
00:15:17,780 --> 00:15:19,830
I love you, Koyori.

206
00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:23,700
He never hesitates to speak his mind.

207
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:24,890
You look really pretty.

208
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:27,620
I love how straightforward he is.

209
00:15:27,620 --> 00:15:30,430
The one I'm dating now is Koyori.

210
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:32,150
I want to cherish the present.

211
00:15:32,150 --> 00:15:35,250
He's so straightforward, it makes me blush.

212
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:39,180
I couldn't even look him in the eye when we first started dating.

213
00:15:39,180 --> 00:15:46,510
If I give others the impression that I don't seem to love Hijiri,

214
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:48,360
then so be it.

215
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:50,880
I'll always understand.

216
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:55,790
As long as Hijiri knows that I love him.

217
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:04,000
So...

218
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:12,390
What is it about Hijiri that you like?

219
00:16:12,390 --> 00:16:15,440
Come again? What are you talking about?

220
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:21,430
I mean, I'd love to know of other good traits Hijiri has, that I haven't noticed.

221
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:29,260
Are you still in junior high or what?

222
00:16:29,260 --> 00:16:33,900
You're acting like we're junior high girls gushing about our favorite seniors!

223
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:37,160
I hate it when someone likes the same person that I do!

224
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:39,550
You want to fight with me? Bring it on!

225
00:16:39,550 --> 00:16:41,560
S-Saito?

226
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:47,620
In short, I don't have any feelings for Hijiri whatsoever.

227
00:16:50,010 --> 00:16:52,680
How can you not fall in love with him?

228
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:59,280
Whatever...

229
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:01,160
I'm really exhausted by all this, Hoshi.

230
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:04,220
You can have this back. Now leave!

231
00:17:04,870 --> 00:17:06,870
Thank you.

232
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:17,150
- I told you not to come without telling me.
- As if telling you would make a difference.

233
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:21,180
Jeez! This is so absurd.

234
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:25,290
- What is?
- Hijiri and Hoshi.

235
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:33,870
The reason for our breakup wasn't exactly a lie.

236
00:17:37,930 --> 00:17:41,960
When Hijiri and I were dating,

237
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:45,680
I noticed that his gaze was always on Hoshi.

238
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:52,420
Later on, I told Hijiri that I wanted to breakup so that I could focus on exams.

239
00:17:52,420 --> 00:17:57,980
- So you were actually...
- That's right. I was testing him.

240
00:18:01,070 --> 00:18:06,200
I test people because I don't trust them.

241
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:09,180
So then? How did he respond?

242
00:18:09,180 --> 00:18:11,230
Hijiri said...

243
00:18:11,230 --> 00:18:12,840
Is that so?

244
00:18:14,710 --> 00:18:18,040
I understand. You'll pass your exams, I'm sure of it.

245
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,280
You have my support.

246
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:26,110
Back then, if I had told him I didn't want to break up after all...

247
00:18:27,290 --> 00:18:29,790
Anyway, it's too late now.

248
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:34,950
But I'm still annoyed.

249
00:18:35,620 --> 00:18:41,030
How can those two be so stupidly trusting of each other? I don't get it.

250
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,900
Where did it go?

251
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:08,350
Woah! Made it in time!

252
00:19:08,350 --> 00:19:10,670
Huh? Hijiri, are you all right?

